README

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TEA-GTK is a powerful and simple-in-use GTK-based text editor for GNU/Linux and *BSD.

2000-2013 Peter Semiletov (tea@list.ru, http://semiletov.org)

http://semiletov.org/tea

There are two separated branches of TEA - main (Qt-based) and old, but renewed one (GTK3-based).
TEA-GTK 17 is GTK2-based, and TEA-GTK 18.x+ is ported to GTK3 with major code cleanup and changes, so TEA-GTK 18+ can be unstable.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
:to run TEA-GTK, use the command "teagtk":
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALLATION AND DEPENDENCIES


Mandatory dependencies: Gtk3, GtkSourceView3, Scons.
Optional: libaspell, zziplib.

To build and install TEA-GTK, run as root at the source top directory:

scons install

To uninstall TEA-GTK, run:

scons uninstall

